# 2D Platformer Game Fixes and Asset Loading Improvements

## Project Overview

This repository showcases selected code contributions I made to a 2D platformer-style game originally developed by **Edward Albert Jaros**.

The game is a Mario-inspired 2D side-scrolling platformer built with **Python** and **Pygame**. It includes a graphical environment, soundtrack, character movement, obstacles, traps, and platform-based navigation where the player must move through the level while avoiding hazards.

My role was focused on final code corrections, safer asset loading, sprite-name normalization, and improving how the game locates files and folders across different project layouts.

